name: ÁNEMOI - Ζεφυρος
description: This is an assemblage of symbols and imaginaries typical of greek mythology. We all wear masks and I think there is nothing better than wearing the mask of a god.The Anemoi are the directional winds. The main winds are Boreas, Zephyros, Notos, and Eurus. This is the third one Zephyros. He is the god of the west wind and spring. He is the gentlest of the winds.
